Here are both approaches using Shell navigation and `IQueryAttributable`:

**1. The Model**

```csharp
public class Product
{
    public string Id { get; set; }
    public string Name { get; set; }
    public decimal Price { get; set; }
}
```

**2. Navigate from ProductListPage (code-behind or VM)**

```csharp
// Approach A: pass just the ID as a string query parameter
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"{nameof(ProductDetailsPage)}?productId={product.Id}");

// Approach B: pass the full object via a dictionary
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync(nameof(ProductDetailsPage),
    new Dictionary<string, object>
    {
        ["product"] = selectedProduct   // passes the actual object
    });
```

**3. ProductDetailsViewModel — receive both with `IQueryAttributable`**

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId { get => _productId; set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value); }
    public Product Product  { get => _product;  set => SetProperty(ref _product, value); }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A: simple string parameter
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // fetch full product from a service, cache, etc.
        }

        // Approach B: full object (passed via dictionary overload)
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**4. Wire up the page**

```csharp
// ProductDetailsPage.xaml.cs
public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
{
    InitializeComponent();
    BindingContext = vm;
}

// MauiProgram.cs — register route + DI
Routing.RegisterRoute(nameof(ProductDetailsPage), typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsPage>();
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsViewModel>();
```

**Key differences:**

| | String query param | Dictionary object |
|---|---|---|
| **Syntax** | `$"route?key={val}"` | `GoToAsync(route, dict)` |
| **Types** | Strings only | Any object |
| **In `ApplyQueryAttributes`** | Value is `string` | Value is your actual type |
| **Use when** | Simple IDs, filters | You already have the object in memory |

Both approaches arrive in the same `ApplyQueryAttributes` method, so you can support either (or both) in one ViewModel.
